i really didnt think that these critters existed, but boy was i wrong. i just thought it was an expression they say to scare the shit out of little kids before they go to sleep. but they came after me. the bed bugs. for 4 weeks now they have been in my room, near my bed area. they first time i noticed something was when i was waking up with bits all over my arms. my first though...hives. and so did my parents. so i was taking all my old allergy stuff, but it wasnt working. then one night at 3 in the morning, i turned on my light, and there it was. the bed bug in the flesh, on my sheets. i freaked. the second i saw that, i went on my laptop and went to google and typed in bed bug. and there was the picture. i searched my bed and killed more. my parents called the bug people, and for 4 weeks, every wednesday they have to come and spray the house. this isnt an easy proses either. all of my clothes are in the bottom of my bed, cause i have the captains bed set. so i have been living out of giant black garbage bags. every week i have to strip my sheets, and my matress must come out of my room. this goes for maureen and jack too. jack had some nests in his bed. maureen had one bug in her room.  well today is 9-15 and the treatments are all over with....well at 3 45 this morning, i found 11 in my bed. i almost shit my pants, i was killing them left and right. so i went to sleep on the couch. my mom found me there and asked why, and i told her bed bugs, and her and my dad ripped apart my bed room. we are getting rid of my wooden captains bed and my desk and everything. i dont have a bed set in my room as im typing this. its ripped apart into pieces sitting on my back porch. were tossin that bitch. we found dead ones on the floor under my bed when cleaning up. so i dont know how long i will have to sleep on the couch for, hopefully not for long. god i feel like when i was in ninth grade, when i had to sleep on the couch for 6 months cause the hurricane destroyed my room. =/ 

p.s.
dont let the bed bugs bit.

new york has got to be hotter or just as hot as florida. back home we have a/c all around....here you have window units, and im dying. on thursday, my cousin took myself, my sister and my mother around the city. in 95 degree weather, i wasnt having fun. it was extremely humid and no breeze. the subways are disgusting, there not clean at all. nothing like you see on the movie screen. then we took a ferry around the island. that cooled me off till i passed out on the ride home.  getting off the ferry my mom didnt call any of her 4 brothers or sisters that live in breezy for a ride....so we ended up hitch hiking. one of the most scariest moments of my life. i dont know how bryan is going to do that all the way to oklahoma or wherever he is going cause i almost shit my pants. anywho, the beaches are nice. rough water and jellyfish up the ying yang. there not red there clear so the itch instead of stinging you. which happen to me already. going to the beach however is a pain in the ass. you dont drive in breezy you walk every where. so you have to load a wagon with all your beach gear and walk all the way there pulling this 30 pound wagon....did i mention threw the sand on the beach as well. so far i have gotten stuck doing it and it sucks f that. i wish it was wabasso everything right there. havent really done anything fun yet with my cousin ryan. he said he was taking me to a club but who knows. he disloacated his shoulder right before i came. oh and hes dating marial streeps daughter. you know the woman who is in mama mia.... he went to the movie premiere on wednesday in the city. lucky bitch.

peace :)

Well its time for the class of 2006 to leave us, im not going to lie...this was an amazing class. At band awards I got upset and and graduation i didnot shed a tear, but today i was driving home and it hit me, there leaving. My mom asked if i was ok and of course i said yes, but really i wasnot. Then I just started to cry my eyes out. I honestly dont know why it hit me out of the blue. My mom asked me if i was going to miss Mike and Allan the most and i said yes. I mean im pretty much going to miss all of them, but Mike and Allan i just got really close with them. We had some really good times together. And on top of them leaving, Allan is leaving the state. My mom said today that Mike and I had a "Love Hate Relationship" and i started to laugh. I remember the first time Mike called I honestly didnot think we would be this good of friends. This entry is prolly totally pointless to those of u if u happen to read this, but livejournal is for venting right?
I kno i keep mentioning my mom but she really was worried about me today cuz i looked so down. i was sitting on the computer playing solitare and she came over and was playing with my hair saying everything is going to be alright. She asked if i had any friends in class of 2007 and i said yea but im not as close with them as i was this year with 06.
It really sucks when one of ur good guy friends are leaving. I told Mike pretty much everything...and now hes leaving. And i know when we tried to hang out ...someone would always call wondering where he is. But i guess that was her job lol
But life goes on and theres nothing i can do. Hopefully they will keep in touch and come over and swim whenever they want.
I had some good times and honestly i will never forget them.

then today in 6th period, my teacher gave me somethin then she walked away, so i called her name but my voice was not coming out of my mouth, i screaming as loud as i can and trying to clear my throat but still nothing. chris lyda was sitting by me playing solitare with me, looking at me like i was stupid, and then someone goes are u sick and i just nodded my head cuz my voice was just not working.

All in all i feel like shit and it sucks cuz normally i never get sick. im taking medicane but i feel like its not working fast enough.
